The paper discusses the implementation of multi-connectivity techniques for mmWave cellular networks, which involves the study of network protocols and solutions at different layers. This makes it likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the physical layer and channel modeling, which suggests the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of mmWave frequencies also indicates the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of blockage and intermittent channel quality, which suggests the Augmented Reality (cs.AR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes solutions for improving the end-to-end performance, which suggests the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
